Analyses of their annual accounts, however, show that many local parties are unable to raise all of the money that they are entitled to spend on such campaigns. This reveals an unhealthy picture of grassroots party organisation in which the capacity to engage effectively with many voters is concentrated in a relatively small number of constituencies and is likely to remain so. This timely and essential book will make a major contribution to the literature on British elections and parties, especially to continuing debates regarding party funding. It will make important reading for academics, students, politicians, civil servants and others interested in this topic.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aCampaign fundszGreat Britain. 0aElectionszGreat Britain. 0aPolitical partieszGreat Britain. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / General.2bisacsh1 aPattie, Charles, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2014z9783111196343oZDB-23-BUPP0 cprintz978144730631340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447306337423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447306337/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-BUPPb2014